It is a ~300 km bidirectional pipe linking Greece to Italy, guaranteeing 100% H2 transportation. Thanks to the connection with other initiatives and local grids, it will provide EU with access to sources from MENA area and global supplies via shipping.

properties.Location: From the offshore location of the Ionian Terminal to the starting point of the H2Poseidon Pipeline. The starting point could change if requested by the outcomes of the surveys (45 km)
properties.Descriptio: Offshore and onshore pipe to connect the Ionian Energy Terminal to the Florovouni Interconnection Point. Thanks to this link, the Terminal will be able to feed the local Greek grid and, through the H2Poseidon Pipeline, the Italian one

properties.Location: Pipeline connecting UK industrial clusters at Teesside, Humberside & Grangemouth & linking up Southampton, the North West and South Wales. Connecting strategic H2 production sites, incl. St Fergus, storage sites and Bacton, connecting UK H2 to EU network
